<TITLE> Turkish PM says 4 dead in Diyarbakir blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ANKARA, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Four people were killed and 52 injured in a blast that ripped through a military vehicle in the southeastern Turkish city of Diyarbakir on Thursday, television channels quoted Prime Minister Tayyip Erdogan as saying. Private broadcaster NTV quoted Diyarbakir's governor as putting the number of those injured in the blast at 68. Diyarbakir is the biggest city of mainly Kurdish southeast Turkey and home to large numbers of troops who are battling PKK Kurdish rebels both inside Turkey and in nearby northern Iraq.
